        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 10:13AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1012 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm over
Cave Springs, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Springdale...                     Withrow Springs State Park...
War Eagle...                      Rogers...
Beaver Lake...                    Elm Springs...
Monte Ne...                       Forum...
Larue...                          Cave Springs...
Bentonville...                    Healing Springs...
Lowell...                         Hobbs State Park...
Centerton...                      Best...
Clifty...                         Lookout...
Sonora...                         Tontitown...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 72 and 87.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
